7:
I can't even see the opposite shore.
It's like an ocean.
11:
It is quiet... Where are the raging
dragons the Guild spoke of?
22:
The name's Remnith. I'm guardian of
this lake. And you, I'm guessing, are
the Guild's puppies.
25:
Well, there's no more bones for you
to chew on, so why don't you run
along home?
29:
I heard there was a whole PACK of
dragons.
33:
Yeah. What you didn't seem to hear
was the "I killed them all" part.
38: Hey, you! Get out of that—
48:
You, uh, shouldn't go wandering into
strange lakes like that. You'll catch
cold.
50:
Why don't you come over to my
place? It's warm and cozy and
perfect for getting to know each
other.
55:
Yes, please. I would like to stay here
a little longer.
66:
As for you UN-lovely gentlemen... get
lost.
71:
Hello? Stella was supposed to come
ALONE?
75:
In your dreams.
...Not even. I'd knock that trash right
out of your head.
79:
Have it your way. It gets pretty cold
after sundown anyways. You're free
to stay one night, but after that,
you're out of here—capiche?
85:
Your home lies in a secluded place...
Do you live alone?
89: No, I have a sister. She's just out now.
95:
Younger. Her name's Enith. Got a
fairy-like ring, doesn't it?
100:
It's the perfect fit. Enith's just the
sweetest little angel, you know?
Cute as a button.
104: Don't even think about hitting on her.
122:
Mmph... Mm? Stella? Is something
wrong?
125:
Remnith isn't here. And I heard
something.
133: It sounded like the roar of a dragon.
137: Gr... "I killed them all," my ass!
152:
Remnith? I thought you had slain all
the dragons!
161:
We mean no harm to that dragon...
To that person.
171: You can tell? This is Enith...
189:
My sister and I guarded the dragons
of this lake. Our family's been
entrusted with the role for
generations.
195:
It all started with old superstitions.
People worshipped dragons
because they were scared of them.
197:
So as musty tradition demanded,
my sister and I lived at the lake with
the lizards.
201:
But we heard the dragons here were
dangerous.
206:
They weren't always. But one day,
they went... funny. They wouldn't
listen to me or Enith anymore. And
they began attacking people.
208:
So I killed them. Some guardian I
am, right?
217:
I thought everything was over. Our
family traditions, our way of living...
But I was wrong.
221:
I don't know if this is a curse or
retribution. All I know is I couldn't
turn my baby sister back.
223:
So, at the very least, I promised to
stay here and protect her for the
rest of our lives... And now, I can't
even do that.
228:
Enith may have gone to another
world.
236:
There are different worlds, and the
World Flipper lets you travel
between them.
239:
We are not certain to find your sister.
But there is hope.
247:
I might not get what you guys are
talking about, but as long as there's
even a chance of finding Enith
again, I'm in!
251:
Hah. Glad to see this skirt-chaser
actually has some direction in life.
254:
Yes. You are welcome to come with
us, Remnith.
260:
Enith, big brother's coming to get
you.
262:
So please... Stop thinking you have
to apologize to me...
